.sh NAME
copydn \*- copy a row down
.sh SYNOPSIS
int
.bd copydn
(area,buffer,ptr)
.s3
int area[30]
.br
int buffer[depth][rlenth]
.br
int ptr[depth]
.s3
int depth
.br
int rlenth
.sh DESCRIPTION
.lp +9 9
area	work area for CXAP
.lp +9 9
buffer	input buffer as supplied to
.it setupb
.lp +9 9
ptr	vector of subscripts as supplied to
.it setupb
.s3
.lp +9 9
depth	maximum number of rows kept in
.it buffer
.lp +9 9
rlenth	maximum number of columns kept in
.it buffer
.i0
.s3
.it Copydn
copies a row in
.it buffer
downward to create the bottom border for a picture
which was opened using
.it setupb.
.it Buffer[ptr[
0]
will be the recipient of the most recently reflected
row when the need arises to create the bottom border of a picture.
.s3
Function value is always +1 indicating success.
